Welcome

This document contains all information related to the 2019 SDP GIS With R Workshop in Atlanta, GA (February 7, 2019). Please refer to this document to find all the information youll need to get set up and get the most out of this workshop, including software, R packages, and additional resources.

Instructors

Roland Richard, Gwinnett County Public Schools

Jared Knowles, Civilytics Consulting, LLC

What do I need to do before the workshop?

You will need to follow these setup instructions:

  1. Install/upgrade software
  2. Install R packages
  3. Set Census API key
  4. Create an example map with the tmap package

1. Install or Upgrade Software

In this workshop, we will use R and RStudio. RStudio is highly recommended, because it makes it easier for most users to work with R Markdown.

Install R

  • A recent version of R (>= 3.5.1 Feather Spray) is recommended. You can check your version from the R Console:
R.version.string
## [1] "R version 3.5.1 (2018-07-02)"

Install RStudio

  • RStudio (>= 1.1.463) is recommended.

Upgrading your system

For more help installing or upgrading R and RStudio, please read through these links:

  1. Maintaining R from What They Forgot to Teach You About R
    • See How to transfer your library when updating R

2. Install R packages

For this workshop, youll need to install several R packages. See below for a guide to installing the packages we will use. Run this code from your R console to install all of the necessary packages:

pkgs_from_cran <- c("sf", "tmap", "tidyverse", "tidycensus", 
                    "leaflet", "mapview","shiny", "ggplot2",
                    "spData", "tigris", "remotes")
install.packages(pkgs_from_cran, dependencies = TRUE)

Check all package installs

rlang::is_installed(c(pkgs_from_cran))

3. Set Census API key

To work with census data in the tidycensus package, you should load the package along with the tidyverse package, and set your Census API key. An API key can be obtained from http://api.census.gov/data/key_signup.html. Follow the code below to set your API key.

## Warning: package 'tidycensus' was built under R version 3.5.2
library(tidycensus)
library(tidyverse)

census_api_key("YOUR API KEY GOES HERE", install = TRUE)

4. Create Example Maps

Lets create a few quick maps . After installing the packages in the preceding step, the following lines of code should create the maps shown below:

Example tmap

A tmap is short for a thematic map - a map that is showing spatial data along some theme.

Example Tigris File Map

You can gain more control over how to make your maps by using shapefiles and ggplot2 directly.

library(tigris)
## Warning: package 'tigris' was built under R version 3.5.2
## To enable 
## caching of data, set `options(tigris_use_cache = TRUE)` in your R script or .Rprofile.
## 
## Attaching package: 'tigris'
## The following object is masked from 'package:graphics':
## 
##     plot
ga_districts <- tigris::school_districts("Georgia", type = "unified", 
                                         year = 2015)
ga_districts <- sf::st_as_sf(ga_districts)

Next Steps

If you successfully produced the two maps above - youre ready for the workshop.

At the workshop well cover how to access geospatial data, geospatial data types, and working with geospatial data to make impactful geospatial visualizations of your data.
